'''RotFront''' (often prefixed with: "Emigrantski Raggamuffin Kollektiv") is a [[world music]] band from [[Berlin]].

== History ==

The group was founded in 2003 as '' Emigrantski Raggamuffin Kollektiv RotFront '' by [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[Yuriy Gurzhy]] together with [[Wladimir Kaminer]] and [[Hungary|Hungarian]] Simon Wahorn.

Other artists occasionally performed with RotFront. The number of musicians on stage sometimes reached fifteen. Actress and singer [[Dorka Gryllus]] is a former band member.

The [[German World Music Award]] Ruth was awarded in 2010 to RotFront for their performance at folk music festival [[TFF Rudolstadt]].<ref>[http://www.weltmusikpreis.de/before/2010.html Ruth 2010] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719114100/http://www.weltmusikpreis.de/before/2010.html |date=2011-07-19 }}</ref>

== Style and background ==

The band plays in various styles including [[Rock music|rock]], [[hip-hop]], [[Dance Hall]], [[reggae]], [[ska]] and a variety of folk backgrounds.

Song lyrics are written in multiple languages, such as [[German language|German]], [[English language|English]], [[Russian language|Russian]] and [[Hungarian language|Hungarian]].

== Discography ==

=== Albums ===

* ''Emigrantski Raggamuffin'' (2009)
* ''Visa free'' (May 2011)
* ''17 German Dances (17 Deutsche Tänze)'' ( April 2014 )

=== Compilations ===

* ''B -Style'' ( compilation contribution to ''listen to berlin'' (Berlin Music Commission) 2009)
* ''Ya Piv (Tiger Hifi Echo Mix)'' ( 2009)
* ''Zhenya ( P-Town Remix)'' ( Compilation contribution to'' Kaffee Burger '' (Duplicate Records) 2006)

